/wonderlist_4x3.png"},{"nm":"2x1","aspRto":2,"url":"https://i.natgeofe.com/n/5fb3be88-fe4f-468a-8a7b-15f3ddd99432/wonderlist_2x1.png"}],"rt":"https://i.natgeofe.com/n/5fb3be88-fe4f-468a-8a7b-15f3ddd99432/wonderlist.png","src":"https://i.natgeofe.com/n/5fb3be88-fe4f-468a-8a7b-15f3ddd99432/wonderlist.png"},"title":"The Wonder List","tags":[{"name":"See the prompts","id":"_none","type":"custom"}],"abTest":{"testId":"ng_pw_copy-287","variantId":"variant_a-1126","type":"paywallTest","variant":"variant_a","abTest":"ng_pw_copy-287*variant_a-1126"}},{"id":"c6963a2b-3d7b-48c7-931a-1de52fb2b40d","cmsType":"RegularStandardPrismTile","isPremium":false,"isEntitled":false,"isUserAuthed":false,"pageType":"home","storyId":"drn:src:natgeo:unison::prod:08a5bb74-19c5-48fa-a536-5c0fdd8ebec4","cId":"c6963a2b-3d7b-48c7-931a-1de52fb2b40d_08a5bb74-19c5-48fa-a536-5c0fdd8ebec4","description":"The end of the historic Artemis II mission kicks off a race to establish a permanent human presence on the moon.","aspectRatio":"3x2","ctas":[{"url":"https://www.nationalgeographic.com/science/article/what-happens-after-artemis-ii","text":"natgeo.ctaText.read","icon":"article"}],"img":{"crps":[{"nm":"raw","aspRto":1.7777777777777777,"url":"https://i.natgeofe.com/n/b4b6af14-4609-4820-872f-a156dcd6a539/2-building-the-moon-base_Page_04.jpg"},{"nm":"16x9","aspRto":1.7777777777777777,"url":"https://i.natgeofe.com/n/b4b6af14-4609-4820-872f-a156dcd6a539/2-building-the-moon-base_Page_04_16x9.jpg"},{"nm":"3x2","aspRto":1.5,"url":"https://i.natgeofe.com/n/b4b6af14-4609-4820-872f-a156dcd6a539/2-building-the-moon-base_Page_04_3x2.jpg"},{"nm":"square","aspRto":1,"url":"https://i.natgeofe.com/n/b4b6af14-4609-4820-872f-a156dcd6a539/2-building-the-moon-base_Page_04_square.jpg"},{"nm":"2x3","aspRto":0.6666666666666666,"url":"https://i.natgeofe.com/n/b4b6af14-4609-4820-872f-a156dcd6a539/2-building-the-moon-base_Page_04_2x3.jpg"},{"nm":"3x4","aspRto":0.75,"url":"https://i.natgeofe.com/n/b4b6af14-4609-4820-872f-a156dcd6a539/2-building-the-moon-base_Page_04_3x4.jpg"},{"nm":"4x3","aspRto":1.3333333333333333,"url":"https://i.natgeofe.com/n/b4b6af14-4609-4820-872f-a156dcd6a539/2-building-the-moon-base_Page_04_4x3.jpg"},{"nm":"2x1","aspRto":2,"url":"https://i.natgeofe.com/n/b4b6af14-4609-4820-872f-a156dcd6a539/2-building-the-moon-base_Page_04_2x1.jpg"}],"rt":"https://i.natgeofe.com/n/b4b6af14-4609-4820-872f-a156dcd6a539/2-building-the-moon-base_Page_04.jpg","src":"https://i.natgeofe.com/n/b4b6af14-4609-4820-872f-a156dcd6a539/2-building-the-moon-base_Page_04.jpg","dsc":"Artist’s concept of Phase 3 of NASA’s Moon Base. NASA is taking bold steps toward establishing a permanent lunar outpost by 2030, in alignment with the President’s Space Superiority Executive Order. The Moon Base will serve as a hub for lunar exploration, scientific research, and technology demonstration, laying the foundation for future missions to Mars and beyond.","ttl":"2-building-the-moon-base_Page_04"},"abstract":"The end of the historic Artemis II mission kicks off a race to establish a permanent human presence on the moon.","title":"What's after Artemis II? Inside NASA's plan to build a moon base.","tags":[{"name":"Artemis II Mission","id":"_none","type":"custom"}],"abTest":{"testId":"ng_pw_copy-287","variantId":"variant_a-1126","type":"paywallTest","variant":"variant_a","abTest":"ng_pw_copy-287*variant_a-1126"}},{"id":"c5f3d247-9645-44f9-a387-5fc9f299a776","cmsType":"RegularStandardPrismTile","isPremium":false,"isEntitled":false,"isUserAuthed":false,"pageType":"home","storyId":"drn:src:natgeo:unison::prod:f334caeb-f281-482d-9975-92369ceb03ff","cId":"c5f3d247-9645-44f9-a387-5fc9f299a776_f334caeb-f281-482d-9975-92369ceb03ff","description":"New science is showing that nature’s vital pollinators are smarter than we ever imagined. Here’s why that discovery should change what we think about one of the world’s most important animals.","aspectRatio":"3x2","ctas":[{"url":"https://www.nationalgeographic.com/animals/article/s