":"473e1ae4-8366-4a27-947b-89467bb07146_bfc58fdb-0fa1-4c7c-9e91-94468ce26611","description":"More than a thousand years after a ship vanished off the coast of modern-day Croatia, archaeologists have uncovered a wreck that might reshape our ideas of the medieval world.","ctas":[{"url":"https://www.nationalgeographic.com/history/article/byzantine-medieval-shipwreck-croatia","text":"natgeo.ctaText.read","icon":"article"}],"img":{"crps":[{"nm":"raw","aspRto":1.374496644295302,"url":"https://i.natgeofe.com/n/cc309d67-67bb-4707-b374-7dd7317c0697/STOCKPKG_MM10254_Byzantine_wreck_80.jpg"},{"nm":"16x9","aspRto":1.7777777777777777,"url":"https://i.natgeofe.com/n/cc309d67-67bb-4707-b374-7dd7317c0697/STOCKPKG_MM10254_Byzantine_wreck_80_16x9.jpg"},{"nm":"3x2","aspRto":1.5,"url":"https://i.natgeofe.com/n/cc309d67-67bb-4707-b374-7dd7317c0697/STOCKPKG_MM10254_Byzantine_wreck_80_3x2.jpg"},{"nm":"square","aspRto":1,"url":"https://i.natgeofe.com/n/cc309d67-67bb-4707-b374-7dd7317c0697/STOCKPKG_MM10254_Byzantine_wreck_80_square.jpg"},{"nm":"2x3","aspRto":0.6666666666666666,"url":"https://i.natgeofe.com/n/cc309d67-67bb-4707-b374-7dd7317c0697/STOCKPKG_MM10254_Byzantine_wreck_80_2x3.jpg"},{"nm":"3x4","aspRto":0.75,"url":"https://i.natgeofe.com/n/cc309d67-67bb-4707-b374-7dd7317c0697/STOCKPKG_MM10254_Byzantine_wreck_80_3x4.jpg"},{"nm":"4x3","aspRto":1.3333333333333333,"url":"https://i.natgeofe.com/n/cc309d67-67bb-4707-b374-7dd7317c0697/STOCKPKG_MM10254_Byzantine_wreck_80_4x3.jpg"},{"nm":"2x1","aspRto":2,"url":"https://i.natgeofe.com/n/cc309d67-67bb-4707-b374-7dd7317c0697/STOCKPKG_MM10254_Byzantine_wreck_80_2x1.jpg"}],"rt":"https://i.natgeofe.com/n/cc309d67-67bb-4707-b374-7dd7317c0697/STOCKPKG_MM10254_Byzantine_wreck_80.jpg","src":"data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mNkYAAAAAYAAjCB0C8AAAAASUVORK5CYII=","dsc":"In 2014 archaeologists found the remains of a ship near Mljet. During a 10-year excavation, they uncovered a trove of golden artifacts that is leading historians to reexamine the so-called Dark Ages.","ttl":"Byzantine Shipwrecks_MM10254-ThreeDivers"},"abstract":"More than a thousand years after a ship vanished off the coast of modern-day Croatia, archaeologists have uncovered a wreck that might reshape our ideas of the medieval world.","title":"Can this medieval shipwreck rewrite ancient history?","tags":[{"name":"History & Culture","id":"b0c8dd52-23a8-34c0-a940-f46792bc9e70","type":"sources","uri":"https://www.nationalgeographic.com/history","tracking":{"data-track-event_name":"content interaction","data-track-module_name":"April 2026 Issue","data-track-module_position_number":10,"data-track-position_number":1,"data-track-placement":"body","data-track-lead_type":"none","data-track-topic_tag":"History & Culture","data-track-link_name":"History & Culture","data-track-link_type":"text"}}],"abTest":{"testId":"ng_pw_copy-287","variantId":"variant_a-1126","type":"paywallTest","variant":"variant_a","abTest":"ng_pw_copy-287*variant_a-1126"}},{"id":"db62fe08-6c50-407d-9c20-facd97825989","cmsType":"RegularImmersivePrismTile","isPremium":false,"isEntitled":false,"isUserAuthed":false,"pageType":"home","storyId":"drn:src:natgeo:unison::prod:e3bc7382-4236-44eb-806b-acdfb5350f26","cId":"db62fe08-6c50-407d-9c20-facd97825989_e3bc7382-4236-44eb-806b-acdfb5350f26","description":"During the mid-20th century, the National Park Service launched the Mission 66 initiative: a bold plan to ditch rustic \"Parkitecture\" and go modern. It took decades for parkgoers to warm up to the audacious style.","ctas":[{"url":"https://www.nationalgeographic.com/travel/article/modernist-architecture-national-parks","text":"natgeo.ctaText.read","icon":"article"}],"img":{"crps":[{"nm":"raw","aspRto":1.2503052503052503,"url":"https://i.natgeofe.com/n/6826082b-316f-437d-99b1-d0855374b63a/great_outsiders_o_davies_032.jpg"},{"nm":"16x9","aspRto":1.7777777777777777,"url":"https://i.natgeofe.com/n/6826082b-316f-437d-99b1-d0855374b63a/great_outsiders_o