ez, an 81-year-old artisan from Santa María Atzompa, in the Mexican state of Oaxaca, is among the craftspeople who make clay animals to be placed on altars during Semana Santa, the Christian Holy Week preceding Easter. The figurines, which sprout bushy chia growth, inspired the enduring American novelty product, the Chia Pet.","ttl":"Hidden History Chia Pets_MM10482-Man"},"abstract":"Long before the suddenly-cool-again ceramic planters were resurrected on TikTok, they played a role in religious culture—one that continues to grow in new ways today.","title":"The secret religious history of your Chia Pet","tags":[{"name":"History & Culture","id":"b0c8dd52-23a8-34c0-a940-f46792bc9e70","type":"sources","uri":"https://www.nationalgeographic.com/history","tracking":{"data-track-event_name":"content interaction","data-track-module_name":"April 2026 Issue","data-track-module_position_number":10,"data-track-link_name":"History & Culture","data-track-link_type":"text","data-track-position_number":7,"data-track-placement":"body","data-track-lead_type":"none","data-track-topic_tag":"History & Culture"}}],"abTest":{"testId":"ng_pw_copy-287","variantId":"variant_a-1126","type":"paywallTest","variant":"variant_a","abTest":"ng_pw_copy-287*variant_a-1126"}},{"id":"f2fdd7d3-2bed-4da1-bc33-1df716ced841","cmsType":"RegularStandardPrismTile","isPremium":false,"isEntitled":false,"isUserAuthed":false,"pageType":"home","storyId":"drn:src:natgeo:unison::prod:e3bc7382-4236-44eb-806b-acdfb5350f26","cId":"f2fdd7d3-2bed-4da1-bc33-1df716ced841_e3bc7382-4236-44eb-806b-acdfb5350f26","description":"During the mid-20th century, the National Park Service launched the Mission 66 initiative: a bold plan to ditch rustic \"Parkitecture\" and go modern. It took decades for parkgoers to warm up to the audacious style.","ctas":[{"url":"https://www.nationalgeographic.com/travel/article/modernist-architecture-national-parks","text":"natgeo.ctaText.read","icon":"article"}],"img":{"crps":[{"nm":"raw","aspRto":1